This file lists all third-party production dependencies of MCP Moira and their
respective licenses. MCP Moira is distributed under the Apache License 2.0.

Full license texts are available in each package's directory under node_modules/,
or from the package's repository URL on the npm registry (https://npmjs.com).

This file was generated with license-checker-rseidelsohn and covers 540 direct
and transitive production dependencies (excludes devDependencies).


LICENSE REMEDIATION NOTES
--------------------------

The following npm overrides are applied in package.json to keep AGPL and UNKNOWN
licensed code out of the production dependency tree and the built Docker image:

  ua-parser-js: pinned to "^1.0.41" (MIT).
    Versions 2.x changed to AGPL-3.0-or-later. The override forces the 1.x MIT
    branch which is a transitive dependency of @daveyplate/better-auth-ui.

  @triplit/client, @triplit/react: overridden to "empty-npm-package" (ISC).
    These are optional provider peer-dependencies of @daveyplate/better-auth-ui
    that we do not use. @triplit/client 1.x is AGPL-3.0-only; @triplit/react
    carries the same dependency. The stub replaces them with an empty no-op
    package (ISC) so no AGPL code is installed or bundled.

  @instantdb/react, @instantdb/core: overridden to "empty-npm-package" (ISC).
    Also optional provider peer-dependencies of @daveyplate/better-auth-ui that
    we do not use. The instantdb npm packages publish without a license field
    (UNKNOWN). The stub removes them from the install tree entirely.

After these overrides the installed tree contains a single empty-npm-package@1.0.0
(ISC) entry that satisfies all four override targets.


